The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | 4 tanneries sealed
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       4 tanneries sealed
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Four more illegal tanneries were sealed on Wednesday, taking the number of such units closed down since Monday to 26.        
	The joint drive  by CESC, pollution control board and the civic body  was launched following an order of the high court and will continue till Thursday. A compliance report will have to be submitted to the court.        
	Of the four tanneries sealed, three were on South Tangra Road and one in the Karaya area.        
	The court had ordered the closure of 14 tanneries in Tiljala, Topsia, Tangra and Karaya and any other that the authorities would come across.        
	We are taking all steps to clean up the area in compliance with the high court order, said S. K. Chaudhary, the additional superintendent of police (industrial), South 24-Parganas.        
	Around 500 tannery employees, led by the CPIs All India Trade Union Congress, blocked the Bypass-Park Circus connector for half an hour to protest the closure. The protesters demanded alternative livelihood.                                                                                                                                                                         
